    <div data-component="article-content">



            <p>It took 14-and-a-half years of walking but finally someone has made it to the edge of the world. Of Minecraft.</p>
<p>That person is Kurt J. Mac, and he began his adventure on 28th March 2011 with one goal in mind: reach the rumoured Far Lands - the theoretical hard edge of a Minecraft world - and on Sunday, 4th October, he made it.</p>
<p>Mac streamed the occasion, as he has streamed every footstep of his adventure so far. He was in a wooden boat at sea and rowed forward, and as he did, a strange wall began to arise before him on the horizon, shaped like a top-down view of a world. This, apparently, is the Far Lands.</p>

<figure>
<p>
<a aria-label="FLoB-a-Thon 2025 - Day 69 - &quot;THE FAR LANDS&quot;" data-platform="youtube" href="https://www.youtube.com/embed/fOS10VEgpuk?autoplay=1" onclick="((e) => { e.preventDefault(); e.currentTarget.closest('.video_wrapper').innerHTML = e.currentTarget.querySelector('template').innerHTML; enableElements(); })(event)" title="Click to play video from YouTube">
<span>FLoB-a-Thon 2025 - Day 69 - "THE FAR LANDS"</span>
